subSubSection.paragraph:
Pectoral fins long ( Fig. 6c ), their length 1.40–1.56 in SL. Tip of pectoral fin in a 90 mm SL juvenile reaching posterior part of dorsal-fin base; in fish 161–181 mm SL extending behind end of dorsal-fin base, sometimes reaching middle of caudal peduncle. First pectoral-fin ray unbranched, its length 2.21–2.85 in SL and 1.57–1.82 in lP. Pelvic-fin base closer to posterior margin of head than to origin of caudal-fin lower lobe ( cV / pV = 0.79–0.83;
cV 1
/ pV = 0.77–0.86). Pelvic fins long, their length strongly decreasing with growth ( Fig. 6d ): in a juvenile 90 mm SL pelvic fin 2.8 in SL and 1.79 in lP ; in fish 161–181 mm SL, 3.19–3.33 in SL and 2.21–2.32 in lP . Tip of pelvic fin in a juvenile 90 mm SL slightly protruding beyond end of anal-fin base; in fish 161–181 mm SL reaching posterior part of anal-fin base.
